1
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:06,988
QUEEN OF TEARS

2
00:01:07,072 --> 00:01:11,242
WHERE IS THE MONEY? WE DEMAND OUR LAND COMPENSATION!

3
00:01:33,681 --> 00:01:34,516
What's going on?

4
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:37,102
Why are they acting up when we're the victims here?

5
00:01:37,185 --> 00:01:38,812
Land compensation?

6
00:01:38,895 --> 00:01:40,980
All hell will break loose if we go home.

7
00:01:41,481 --> 00:01:42,315
Let's go back.

8
00:01:42,398 --> 00:01:45,110
Where can we go if not home?

9
00:01:45,193 --> 00:01:46,945
We can't go to a hotel.

10
00:01:51,241 --> 00:01:52,450
Hey, Grace.

11
00:01:52,534 --> 00:01:56,412
Ma'am, the back gate is empty. You can come this way.

12
00:01:57,413 --> 00:01:59,666
You're the best. Okay.

13
00:02:00,792 --> 00:02:02,585
Turn back. Take the back gate.

14
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:10,093
So? Are they coming?

15
00:02:11,136 --> 00:02:12,262
Let's see what you can do.

16
00:02:12,345 --> 00:02:15,431
"A conglomerate family becomes dirt-poor and gets kicked out."

17
00:02:17,809 --> 00:02:19,060
Here they come!

18
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,152
What are you doing? Open the gate.

19
00:02:27,235 --> 00:02:30,530
Ma'am, you need to step out for a bit.

20
00:02:36,452 --> 00:02:38,788
What is it? I'm tired.

21
00:02:38,872 --> 00:02:42,167
Are you aware that Chairman Hong gave Ms. Moh the power of attorney

22
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:46,129
to manage everything in Queens Town

23
00:02:46,212 --> 00:02:48,631
during his absence?

24
00:02:49,424 --> 00:02:50,550
So?

25
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:53,219
Is she kicking us out?

26
00:02:53,303 --> 00:02:55,513
Not really.

27
00:02:55,597 --> 00:02:57,932
Given how this place is swarming

28
00:02:58,016 --> 00:02:59,726
with reporters and protesters,

29
00:02:59,809 --> 00:03:04,063
she wants you to lie low until the dust settles.

30
00:03:04,147 --> 00:03:07,609
Does she have the right to do that? We're all residents here.

31
00:03:07,692 --> 00:03:08,693
Shut up, will you?

32
00:03:09,861 --> 00:03:11,738
Don't butt in when the adults are talking.

33
00:03:12,447 --> 00:03:14,616
What did you just say?

34
00:03:14,699 --> 00:03:16,367
Damn it.

35
00:03:17,035 --> 00:03:19,412
You don't get it, do you?

36
00:03:25,460 --> 00:03:27,378
Wait. Hey.

37
00:03:28,546 --> 00:03:30,048
Company vehicles, drivers,

38
00:03:30,131 --> 00:03:32,800
phones, and credit cards are no longer yours.

39
00:03:33,801 --> 00:03:36,512
Your company security cards and key cards won't work either.

40
00:03:36,596 --> 00:03:38,890
What do you mean? It's my house!

41
00:03:38,973 --> 00:03:40,850
Call the police, honey!

42
00:03:40,934 --> 00:03:42,393
Sure, call them.

43
00:03:42,477 --> 00:03:44,103
The reporters would love it.

44
00:03:44,187 --> 00:03:45,980
Given our history together,

45
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:48,900
I've packed up some essentials for you.

46
00:03:49,651 --> 00:03:50,985
So get going.

47
00:03:59,661 --> 00:04:01,746
-What's that? -Damn it.

48
00:04:03,248 --> 00:04:04,999
Get in! There are cameras on the other side!

49
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,301
Isn't this absurd, Hyun-woo?

50
00:04:15,385 --> 00:04:16,261
How can Seul-hee

51
00:04:16,344 --> 00:04:18,346
lock the doors and kick us out

52
00:04:18,429 --> 00:04:19,639
of our father's house?

53
00:04:19,722 --> 00:04:22,308
You can assert your rights as residents of the house.

54
00:04:22,392 --> 00:04:24,936
But you must file a lawsuit,

55
00:04:25,019 --> 00:04:26,562
and it'll take some time.

56
00:04:27,313 --> 00:04:28,606
But the biggest issue is

57
00:04:28,690 --> 00:04:31,401
the chairman included a convertible rights clause in the contract

58
00:04:31,484 --> 00:04:34,070
and put his family as joint surety.

59
00:04:34,153 --> 00:04:36,948
So your real estate, stocks, and personal bank accounts

60
00:04:37,031 --> 00:04:37,907
are all frozen.

61
00:04:39,284 --> 00:04:41,160
Gosh, Father.

62
00:04:42,287 --> 00:04:44,872
Hold on. Is this true, honey?

63
00:04:46,082 --> 00:04:48,084
I didn't know either. I'm flustered too.

64
00:04:49,210 --> 00:04:50,169
Lip balm, anyone?

65
00:04:50,253 --> 00:04:53,172
Lip balm, my foot.

66
00:04:53,256 --> 00:04:57,510
It's best that the media doesn't post photos of you.

67
00:04:57,593 --> 00:05:01,097
I'll take you somewhere safe, and we can think of our next plan there.

68
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:03,891
Why has Soo-cheol been so quiet?

69
00:05:03,975 --> 00:05:06,686
Hey, Soo-cheol! Say something!

70
00:05:06,769 --> 00:05:10,273
So your wife, Da-hye, was in on this too. Am I right?

71
00:05:11,149 --> 00:05:14,402
What did I say? Geon-u doesn't take after him at all!

72
00:05:14,485 --> 00:05:15,486
Come on.

73
00:05:22,994 --> 00:05:25,913
By the way, where are we going?

74
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:28,791
Well…

75
00:05:46,517 --> 00:05:47,894
-What is that? -What's that?

76
00:05:47,977 --> 00:05:48,936
What?

77
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:50,938
-Who's blinding us? -Who's that?

78
00:05:54,692 --> 00:05:56,486
-Wait. -Who's that?

79
00:05:56,569 --> 00:05:58,237
This is private property.

80
00:05:58,321 --> 00:05:59,947
-What? -Is that Hyun-woo?

81
00:06:01,574 --> 00:06:02,700
Who?

82
00:06:02,784 --> 00:06:03,659
Hyun-woo.

83
00:06:03,743 --> 00:06:05,370
Hey, Hyun-woo!

84
00:06:05,453 --> 00:06:07,538
I didn't know you were coming.

85
00:06:07,622 --> 00:06:09,749
Dad, it was urgent.

86
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:13,461
Hey, Hyun-woo. Why weren't you picking up?

87
00:06:13,544 --> 00:06:16,381
Do you not eat well?

88
00:06:16,464 --> 00:06:18,091
You look terrible.

89
00:06:18,174 --> 00:06:20,176
-No, it's-- -Don't be so distraught.

90
00:06:20,259 --> 00:06:21,928
I'm glad you left that crazy family.

91
00:06:22,011 --> 00:06:25,098
Look at what happened to them after they kicked you out.

92
00:06:25,181 --> 00:06:26,682
Karma will always find its way.

93
00:06:26,766 --> 00:06:28,142
-Hold on-- -You bet.

94
00:06:28,226 --> 00:06:30,728
I was so relieved to hear

95
00:06:30,812 --> 00:06:33,147
that the damn family was ruined. Serves them right!

96
00:06:33,231 --> 00:06:37,193
Anyway, forget about that sly fox and live a happy life.

97
00:06:46,577 --> 00:06:49,122
The sly fox is here too.

98
00:06:51,207 --> 00:06:52,375
I see.

99
00:06:53,376 --> 00:06:55,044
You're here too.

100
00:06:56,963 --> 00:06:58,631
It's not just her.

101
00:07:31,038 --> 00:07:32,081
Goodness.

102
00:07:32,748 --> 00:07:34,792
It's your father-in-law. No.

103
00:07:34,876 --> 00:07:37,086
Is it "former father-in-law"?

104
00:07:38,296 --> 00:07:40,798
Anyway… What brings you here?

105
00:07:40,882 --> 00:07:41,716
Hello.

106
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,385
How have you been?

107
00:07:44,469 --> 00:07:45,470
Good.

108
00:07:46,179 --> 00:07:47,763
Say hello.

109
00:07:49,474 --> 00:07:50,850
-Hello. -Hello.

110
00:07:51,684 --> 00:07:53,686
I apologize for coming unannounced.

111
00:07:53,769 --> 00:07:55,021
Don't worry about it.

112
00:07:56,022 --> 00:07:57,023
I'm glad you're here.

113
00:07:57,940 --> 00:08:00,735
Please follow me. This way.

114
00:08:00,818 --> 00:08:01,861
I'm going back to Seoul.

115
00:08:01,944 --> 00:08:03,237
-Hail a cab. -Mom.

116
00:08:03,321 --> 00:08:06,616
There are no cabs around here at this hour.

117
00:08:06,699 --> 00:08:10,620
Then I'll find another way, so do as you please.

118
00:08:11,579 --> 00:08:12,663
Honey.

119
00:08:13,831 --> 00:08:14,957
Honey.

120
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:17,627
We're already here, though.

121
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:20,296
I already told you that I didn't want to come.

122
00:08:20,379 --> 00:08:22,298
Jeez!

123
00:08:30,181 --> 00:08:31,182
What's wrong?

124
00:08:31,974 --> 00:08:34,310
I think she stepped on cow dung.

125
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,570
Mom, don't come. Don't come to me!

126
00:08:44,654 --> 00:08:46,197
Don't come to me either!

127
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,121
Ms. Kim?

128
00:09:24,235 --> 00:09:25,778
That's good.

129
00:09:33,244 --> 00:09:34,412
Hey, Hyeon-tae.

130
00:09:36,289 --> 00:09:37,290
I picked plenty.

131
00:09:37,832 --> 00:09:39,584
How am I to make sense of this?

132
00:09:40,167 --> 00:09:41,002
What do you mean?

133
00:09:41,085 --> 00:09:44,964
Why did Hyun-woo bring his ex-wife and her family all the way here?

134
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,133
It's similar to Korea.

135
00:09:47,842 --> 00:09:49,468
There may be North and South,

136
00:09:49,552 --> 00:09:52,930
but we're still on the same team at the Olympics.

137
00:09:53,014 --> 00:09:54,056
What are you saying?

138
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,601
We join hands when there's a common enemy.

139
00:09:57,977 --> 00:10:01,731
Does this mean they might get back together?

140
00:10:01,814 --> 00:10:05,443
We may be on the same team, but that doesn't guarantee a unification.

141
00:10:08,654 --> 00:10:10,281
-Let's get ready. -Okay.

142
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:23,377
What's wrong?

143
00:10:26,547 --> 00:10:27,882
Thank you for today.

144
00:10:28,633 --> 00:10:30,384
I'll look for a new place to go to tomorrow.

145
00:10:30,468 --> 00:10:31,886
Nothing will change

146
00:10:31,969 --> 00:10:33,387
overnight.

147
00:10:34,347 --> 00:10:37,308
I know. All the more reason why we shouldn't stay here.

148
00:10:37,892 --> 00:10:39,644
It'll take some time until the dust settles.

149
00:10:39,727 --> 00:10:42,772
This is the safest and the most comfortable place you can be.

150
00:10:45,316 --> 00:10:46,609
Not for me.

151
00:10:47,276 --> 00:10:49,612
I'm at my former in-laws' house.

152
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:54,408
Not you. Me.

153
00:10:55,242 --> 00:10:56,869
This is comfortable for me.

154
00:10:59,580 --> 00:11:00,581
Let me…

155
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:03,959
be selfish for now.

156
00:11:05,169 --> 00:11:07,421
I have too much on my plate right now

157
00:11:07,505 --> 00:11:09,340
to worry about you as well.

158
00:11:10,132 --> 00:11:11,384
Don't worry about me.

159
00:11:12,343 --> 00:11:13,803
We're divorced.

160
00:11:14,679 --> 00:11:16,305
Whatever happens to me

161
00:11:16,389 --> 00:11:17,765
or my family

162
00:11:17,848 --> 00:11:20,393
has nothing to do with you.

163
00:11:31,987 --> 00:11:33,531
I'll stop worrying

164
00:11:35,449 --> 00:11:36,784
once you're better.

165
00:11:41,914 --> 00:11:42,957
But for now,

166
00:11:44,875 --> 00:11:45,918
that's impossible.

167
00:11:46,544 --> 00:11:47,628
So please…

168
00:11:50,339 --> 00:11:51,257
understand.

169
00:11:54,218 --> 00:11:55,344
Just…

170
00:11:56,429 --> 00:11:57,638
stay with me.

171
00:12:04,061 --> 00:12:05,563
Do you think being together

172
00:12:05,646 --> 00:12:07,606
in this situation will make us happier?

173
00:12:07,690 --> 00:12:08,858
We'll be less miserable.

174
00:12:10,025 --> 00:12:12,445
Don't think too much for today.

175
00:12:14,029 --> 00:12:16,991
Let's just focus on being less miserable.

176
00:12:32,006 --> 00:12:34,258
I got rid of the chunks. As for the smell…

177
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:38,053
It'll take some time to dry.

178
00:12:39,722 --> 00:12:41,849
-Just throw them away. -Goodness.

179
00:12:42,850 --> 00:12:45,144
What for? They look expensive.

180
00:12:51,609 --> 00:12:53,068
Wear these for now.

181
00:13:20,095 --> 00:13:22,765
What about these heels? Should I throw them away?

182
00:13:24,642 --> 00:13:26,101
So what is it?

183
00:13:26,185 --> 00:13:28,187
Will she get rid of them or not?

184
00:13:29,313 --> 00:13:30,356
They look expensive.

185
00:13:30,439 --> 00:13:31,774
Over 500,000 won.

186
00:13:43,661 --> 00:13:44,829
Five million?

187
00:13:59,802 --> 00:14:01,512
I didn't come here by choice.

188
00:14:03,180 --> 00:14:05,140
Your son was very quick.

189
00:14:05,224 --> 00:14:07,351
He practically kidnapped us.

190
00:14:07,434 --> 00:14:09,019
My late mother

191
00:14:09,562 --> 00:14:11,480
was right.

192
00:14:11,564 --> 00:14:14,358
She said, "You never know what the future holds."

193
00:14:15,442 --> 00:14:20,239
Who knew we'd meet again a few days after we bid our last farewell?

194
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:25,786
My sister is urging us to stay at her villa in Namhae instead.

195
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,621
We'll leave first thing in the morning.

196
00:14:29,164 --> 00:14:30,291
Sure.

197
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:34,295
But don't be so confident.

198
00:14:55,941 --> 00:14:56,775
Sir.

199
00:14:57,484 --> 00:14:58,319
Please eat.

200
00:14:59,737 --> 00:15:00,571
Okay.

201
00:15:32,436 --> 00:15:33,312
It's tasty.

202
00:15:35,272 --> 00:15:36,482
Does it suit your taste?

203
00:15:38,359 --> 00:15:40,277
Yes, it's very delicious.

204
00:15:42,905 --> 00:15:43,906
Eat up.

205
00:15:44,615 --> 00:15:46,825
You need to cut down on sodium.

206
00:15:46,909 --> 00:15:50,162
Doctor Yoon will scold you if he finds out. Don't eat that.

207
00:15:50,245 --> 00:15:53,332
Don't worry. He hasn't been answering my calls.

208
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:55,125
I think he blocked me.

209
00:16:00,965 --> 00:16:04,885
Why aren't you eating, Soo-cheol?

210
00:16:13,143 --> 00:16:14,144
I'm sorry.

211
00:16:14,853 --> 00:16:16,105
I'm not hungry.

212
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:18,065
Do you have water?

213
00:16:18,148 --> 00:16:19,858
Yes, here.

214
00:16:19,942 --> 00:16:21,068
Here you go.

215
00:16:22,569 --> 00:16:24,446
You see…

216
00:16:24,530 --> 00:16:26,365
I only drink sealed water.

217
00:16:26,448 --> 00:16:27,825
Do you have bottled water?

218
00:16:28,784 --> 00:16:30,661
Hey, just drink it.

219
00:16:34,039 --> 00:16:36,333
Yes, we have some at the store. I'll bring some.

220
00:16:36,417 --> 00:16:39,837
Thank you. I'd prefer mineral water from the Alps, please.

221
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:45,551
Sorry? The Alps?

222
00:16:46,677 --> 00:16:48,095
I can't believe you.

223
00:16:50,514 --> 00:16:51,640
I apologize.

224
00:16:51,724 --> 00:16:53,308
He's still immature.

225
00:16:53,392 --> 00:16:55,269
Gosh, that's okay.

226
00:16:55,352 --> 00:16:56,603
We understand.

227
00:16:57,563 --> 00:16:59,982
It doesn't have to be from the Alps.

228
00:17:00,065 --> 00:17:04,028
Germany or Australia is fine.

229
00:17:04,111 --> 00:17:05,529
Fiji is okay too.

230
00:17:05,612 --> 00:17:09,116
We're not that picky.

231
00:17:10,576 --> 00:17:13,245
Yes, I'm fine with them too.

232
00:17:16,832 --> 00:17:18,792
Just drink from the kettle!

233
00:17:27,342 --> 00:17:28,343
I'll take that.

234
00:17:28,427 --> 00:17:30,596
-Gosh. -No, please.

235
00:17:32,598 --> 00:17:33,807
She doesn't hit me.

236
00:17:39,229 --> 00:17:41,023
Did you see her hit her brother?

237
00:17:41,106 --> 00:17:42,399
I was terrified.

238
00:17:42,483 --> 00:17:44,443
What do you mean? You hit me too.

239
00:17:44,526 --> 00:17:47,529
Hey, my slaps aren't that painful.

240
00:17:47,613 --> 00:17:50,115
But Hae-in was totally--

241
00:17:50,199 --> 00:17:51,450
Should I help?

242
00:17:52,618 --> 00:17:53,452
Gosh.

243
00:17:54,161 --> 00:17:56,121
That's okay.

244
00:17:56,205 --> 00:17:58,665
No, you don't need to help. You can just rest.

245
00:18:01,668 --> 00:18:02,878
Thank you.

246
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:06,090
By the way, Hae-in…

247
00:18:07,174 --> 00:18:08,383
Right.

248
00:18:08,467 --> 00:18:10,135
Can I say something?

249
00:18:10,219 --> 00:18:11,762
Even though you two are divorced…

250
00:18:12,930 --> 00:18:13,972
Sure, you can.

251
00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:17,017
Don't take to heart what I said earlier.

252
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:18,811
Which was?

253
00:18:19,311 --> 00:18:21,021
About you being a sly fox and all.

254
00:18:21,605 --> 00:18:24,650
-Right. -I never disliked sly foxes.

255
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:27,027
After all, that was my nickname in high school.

256
00:18:27,111 --> 00:18:28,821
I look like a fox, you know?

257
00:18:28,904 --> 00:18:32,533
I'd like to apologize for saying that your family was ruined.

258
00:18:32,616 --> 00:18:34,493
It's true though.

259
00:18:34,576 --> 00:18:35,953
We're done for.

260
00:18:36,411 --> 00:18:37,996
This is a touchy subject.

261
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:39,832
I know you're divorced,

262
00:18:39,915 --> 00:18:41,416
but did you agree to come here

263
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:43,418
because you had feelings for each other?

264
00:18:43,502 --> 00:18:44,670
No.

265
00:18:44,753 --> 00:18:46,964
It was an emergency. Nothing more.

266
00:18:47,464 --> 00:18:48,715
Right. You're strangers now.

267
00:18:48,799 --> 00:18:50,092
We're more than that.

268
00:18:50,175 --> 00:18:52,177
But could there be something between you--

269
00:18:52,261 --> 00:18:53,178
No, not at all.

270
00:18:53,887 --> 00:18:55,097
I see.

271
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:58,976
We wouldn't have divorced if that was the case.

272
00:18:59,059 --> 00:19:00,519
That's true.

273
00:19:00,602 --> 00:19:02,104
She's right.

274
00:19:02,187 --> 00:19:04,273
So please don't misunderstand, anticipate,

275
00:19:04,356 --> 00:19:06,441
or give meaning to any of this.

276
00:19:08,652 --> 00:19:11,613
I won't. Remember So-yeong?

277
00:19:11,697 --> 00:19:12,698
The principal's daughter?

278
00:19:12,781 --> 00:19:15,492
She recently got a job at a middle school nearby

279
00:19:15,576 --> 00:19:18,203
and has been asking for Hyun-woo's number.

280
00:19:18,287 --> 00:19:20,372
-But I couldn't tell her. -You can.

281
00:19:21,123 --> 00:19:21,999
Can I?

282
00:19:24,918 --> 00:19:28,463
But then again, I didn't need to ask for permission.

283
00:19:29,631 --> 00:19:30,549
Good night then.

284
00:19:34,469 --> 00:19:35,304
I knew it.

285
00:19:35,387 --> 00:19:36,972
They won't get back together.

286
00:19:37,055 --> 00:19:39,141
Hey, I don't want that either.

287
00:19:39,224 --> 00:19:40,475
She's so rude.

288
00:19:40,559 --> 00:19:44,688
She didn't bother to hear me out and kept cutting me off.

289
00:19:44,771 --> 00:19:47,649
Jeez, that sly fox. She shouldn't have come.

290
00:19:50,736 --> 00:19:53,155
This is our annex.

291
00:19:53,238 --> 00:19:56,408
We used to live here before Hyeon-tae and Mi-seon

292
00:19:56,491 --> 00:19:57,951
got married.

293
00:19:58,035 --> 00:19:59,912
We heated up the floor.

294
00:20:02,456 --> 00:20:04,416
I'm sorry about everything.

295
00:20:04,499 --> 00:20:05,334
Goodness.

296
00:20:05,417 --> 00:20:06,919
Please don't apologize.

297
00:20:07,002 --> 00:20:09,004
Even neighbors help out

298
00:20:09,087 --> 00:20:10,589
when times are rough.

299
00:20:11,548 --> 00:20:12,841
But we

300
00:20:13,592 --> 00:20:16,053
used to be family.

301
00:20:16,637 --> 00:20:19,973
Hyun-woo told me that it's a secret that you're here.

302
00:20:20,057 --> 00:20:21,892
I already warned the villagers

303
00:20:21,975 --> 00:20:25,395
not to use the internet.

304
00:20:25,479 --> 00:20:27,773
There are no CCTV cameras around,

305
00:20:27,856 --> 00:20:32,444
and barely anyone uses a smartphone here.

306
00:20:32,527 --> 00:20:36,323
So don't you worry and have a good night's sleep.

307
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:39,451
Thank you so much.

308
00:20:39,534 --> 00:20:41,620
Gosh, it's nothing.

309
00:20:44,122 --> 00:20:46,500
You can wash up in here.

310
00:20:47,584 --> 00:20:48,418
Where's the tub?

311
00:20:48,502 --> 00:20:49,461
There is none.

312
00:20:49,544 --> 00:20:52,714
But here's the shower.

313
00:21:00,514 --> 00:21:01,515
Where can I take a bath?

314
00:21:01,598 --> 00:21:02,516
You can't.

315
00:21:02,599 --> 00:21:04,726
-What about my bath bomb? -Don't use it.

316
00:21:07,312 --> 00:21:09,523
You can use this towel.

317
00:21:10,482 --> 00:21:11,650
BAEK HO-YEOL'S FIRST BIRTHDAY

318
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:15,779
Didn't you say your nephew's name was Ho-yeol?

319
00:21:15,862 --> 00:21:16,947
Yes, Baek Ho-yeol.

320
00:21:19,491 --> 00:21:21,952
This "baby Ho-yeol" can't possibly be

321
00:21:22,035 --> 00:21:24,746
the boy I saw earlier, right?

322
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:28,583
I see.

323
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:33,005
Right. He used to be so tiny.

324
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:36,425
He was so adorable. Yes, this is him.

325
00:21:37,843 --> 00:21:39,261
So it's the same person.

326
00:21:39,845 --> 00:21:42,806
Then how old is this towel?

327
00:21:44,057 --> 00:21:45,017
Gosh.

328
00:21:45,851 --> 00:21:47,853
What's wrong? Do you want a new one?

329
00:21:50,188 --> 00:21:51,023
Hyun-woo.

330
00:21:52,149 --> 00:21:53,817
Do you know

331
00:21:55,444 --> 00:21:58,488
what's even more unbelievable than this eight-year-old towel?

332
00:22:00,407 --> 00:22:01,408
It's that

333
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,746
Da-hye and Geon-u have left me.

334
00:22:07,122 --> 00:22:11,668
And that Yoon Eun-sung, that bastard deceived me!

335
00:22:17,883 --> 00:22:18,967
What's going on?

336
00:22:19,051 --> 00:22:20,594
Where is everyone?

337
00:22:22,262 --> 00:22:23,263
Hello.

338
00:22:24,014 --> 00:22:25,891
Where's Hae-in's family?

339
00:22:27,142 --> 00:22:27,976
I wouldn't know.

340
00:22:28,060 --> 00:22:30,020
I'm sure they're somewhere.

341
00:22:30,103 --> 00:22:31,313
Why did you do it?

342
00:22:34,524 --> 00:22:36,735
Did you want them to stay then?

343
00:22:36,818 --> 00:22:38,278
How can we possibly live

344
00:22:38,362 --> 00:22:40,781
under the same roof as those we stole from?

345
00:22:40,864 --> 00:22:42,199
It's not over yet.

346
00:22:42,282 --> 00:22:44,743
They'll try to find your weakness

347
00:22:44,826 --> 00:22:46,536
and retaliate.

348
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:48,121
You should've just kept them close--

349
00:22:48,205 --> 00:22:49,081
Don't you…

350
00:22:49,664 --> 00:22:51,666
just want to keep Hae-in close?

351
00:22:52,334 --> 00:22:53,377
Forget her.

352
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,961
You will do so eventually.

353
00:22:55,045 --> 00:22:56,755
Don't bother regretting it.

354
00:23:01,593 --> 00:23:03,804
I've lived here for 25 years,

355
00:23:04,596 --> 00:23:06,765
but this is the first time I get to pick

356
00:23:06,848 --> 00:23:08,350
my own wine.

357
00:23:10,602 --> 00:23:12,604
Let's enjoy what we have from now on.

358
00:23:12,687 --> 00:23:13,522
Okay?

359
00:23:15,107 --> 00:23:17,609
Remember what you said when you sent me away?

360
00:23:19,194 --> 00:23:20,028
Don't forget.

361
00:23:21,029 --> 00:23:23,115
I love you the most.

362
00:23:24,825 --> 00:23:26,284
So I'll stay strong and endure it

363
00:23:26,368 --> 00:23:27,828
even when I miss you

364
00:23:28,620 --> 00:23:30,080
and want to see you.

365
00:23:31,123 --> 00:23:32,833
Just because I love you.

366
00:23:34,793 --> 00:23:37,587
And you kept your word. You were pretty good at it.

367
00:23:38,463 --> 00:23:42,551
You were never curious about how your young son was doing abroad.

368
00:23:42,634 --> 00:23:45,220
You never bothered to call. You really endured it all.

369
00:23:45,303 --> 00:23:46,471
But, you see,

370
00:23:47,180 --> 00:23:48,723
I realized that it was a lie…

371
00:23:51,435 --> 00:23:54,104
to endure something out of love.

372
00:23:55,063 --> 00:23:56,273
You can't endure it

373
00:23:57,524 --> 00:23:58,692
if you truly love someone.

374
00:24:07,075 --> 00:24:08,285
What are you getting at?

375
00:24:09,244 --> 00:24:10,245
Are you saying

376
00:24:10,829 --> 00:24:11,997
that you resent me now?

377
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:12,914
No.

378
00:24:12,998 --> 00:24:15,959
I'm telling you that I'll bring Hae-in back here at all costs.

379
00:24:16,042 --> 00:24:17,544
I'm not like you.

380
00:24:17,627 --> 00:24:21,298
It drives me crazy to wonder where she is and what she's doing.

381
00:24:24,176 --> 00:24:25,177
I can't

382
00:24:26,845 --> 00:24:27,679
endure it.

383
00:24:29,931 --> 00:24:32,684
Do you even know how difficult it was to come this far?

384
00:24:32,767 --> 00:24:34,811
Why do you think I'm doing this?

385
00:24:39,107 --> 00:24:41,151
We don't share the same goal.

386
00:24:41,234 --> 00:24:43,570
So just like how you chose this family over me,

387
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:46,156
I can also choose

388
00:24:47,282 --> 00:24:49,075
something else over you.

389
00:25:06,218 --> 00:25:08,512
Check all the hotels and villas.

390
00:25:13,934 --> 00:25:15,352
This is a living hell.

391
00:25:17,145 --> 00:25:19,648
What kind of hell offers us a silk blanket

392
00:25:20,398 --> 00:25:22,651
and a warm floor?

393
00:25:36,831 --> 00:25:37,874
Let him be.

394
00:25:38,750 --> 00:25:41,127
He must be utterly distraught.

395
00:25:44,047 --> 00:25:47,634
He's never slept on hard floors before.

396
00:25:47,717 --> 00:25:51,513
He can only sleep on Spanish royal beds.

397
00:25:55,267 --> 00:25:58,311
Ours looks thicker than his.

398
00:25:59,062 --> 00:26:00,355
Let's switch blankets.

399
00:26:01,064 --> 00:26:01,898
Honey.

400
00:26:03,024 --> 00:26:04,025
What?

401
00:26:04,109 --> 00:26:05,151
Me too.

402
00:26:06,611 --> 00:26:09,030
It's my first time sleeping on the floor too.

403
00:26:12,826 --> 00:26:14,911
I'm from a rich family too.

404
00:26:25,589 --> 00:26:26,590
Hello?

405
00:26:27,465 --> 00:26:28,883
-Beom-seok. -I saw the news.

406
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:30,802
How's everyone?

407
00:26:30,885 --> 00:26:32,053
A total mess.

408
00:26:33,221 --> 00:26:36,224
I feel terrible for Father.

409
00:26:37,434 --> 00:26:39,352
I'm hanging up if this is about him.

410
00:26:39,436 --> 00:26:42,230
Don't be like this.

411
00:26:42,314 --> 00:26:43,607
Remember what he said?

412
00:26:43,690 --> 00:26:45,900
He told me not to even come to his funeral.

413
00:26:45,984 --> 00:26:48,486
So don't call me even if he passes away.

414
00:26:48,570 --> 00:26:50,989
Come on. Don't be like this.

415
00:26:53,033 --> 00:26:56,036
I resented him when he was healthy.

416
00:26:58,371 --> 00:26:59,998
But now that he's ill,

417
00:27:01,249 --> 00:27:03,168
I feel so guilty.

418
00:27:03,251 --> 00:27:04,085
For what?

419
00:27:07,088 --> 00:27:09,299
Maybe everything would've been okay

420
00:27:11,468 --> 00:27:14,137
had I treated Seul-hee better.

421
00:27:14,220 --> 00:27:17,766
Maybe she was livid because I mistreated her.

422
00:27:18,350 --> 00:27:19,643
About ten years ago,

423
00:27:19,726 --> 00:27:21,770
I threw a huge fit when Father told me

424
00:27:21,853 --> 00:27:23,355
he wanted her to be his legal wife.

425
00:27:23,438 --> 00:27:25,023
So he gave up on that idea.

426
00:27:25,649 --> 00:27:28,443
Maybe she held a grudge and schemed everything.

427
00:27:32,697 --> 00:27:35,325
This stupid ring. It's nothing.

428
00:27:35,408 --> 00:27:37,285
I should've just let her have it.

429
00:27:40,288 --> 00:27:41,998
Should I give it back to her?

430
00:27:42,957 --> 00:27:45,752
Should I give it to her right now?

431
00:27:49,172 --> 00:27:50,340
Beom-ja.

432
00:27:51,883 --> 00:27:55,679
It feels like I'm to blame for what happened to Father.

433
00:28:08,566 --> 00:28:11,277
Why are you crying? Did your husband leave you?

434
00:28:12,445 --> 00:28:15,073
-No. -Then, are your parents ill?

435
00:28:18,451 --> 00:28:19,452
Yes…

436
00:28:20,870 --> 00:28:24,082
My father is sick.

437
00:28:24,165 --> 00:28:25,375
Oh, dear.

438
00:28:26,668 --> 00:28:28,503
It's normal to feel guilty

439
00:28:28,586 --> 00:28:31,631
when your parent falls ill.

440
00:28:32,507 --> 00:28:33,341
Cry.

441
00:28:33,425 --> 00:28:35,593
Let it all out and treat him better from now on.

442
00:28:36,261 --> 00:28:37,470
Everything will be fine.

443
00:28:39,013 --> 00:28:41,057
Thank you.

444
00:28:43,852 --> 00:28:45,270
Mom!

445
00:28:46,646 --> 00:28:47,731
Mom!

446
00:28:47,814 --> 00:28:50,275
Goodness, what do I do?

447
00:28:51,151 --> 00:28:52,902
What's the matter?

448
00:28:54,028 --> 00:28:58,450
There's this lunatic who calls me Mom and follows me around.

449
00:28:58,533 --> 00:28:59,409
What?

450
00:28:59,492 --> 00:29:02,537
Can you tell him that you're my daughter?

451
00:29:04,414 --> 00:29:05,957
Okay.

452
00:29:07,459 --> 00:29:08,668
Mom.

453
00:29:09,878 --> 00:29:11,713
It's too late to be out.

454
00:29:14,466 --> 00:29:17,927
Excuse me. This is my mom.

455
00:29:18,011 --> 00:29:19,929
-So go on your way. -What?

456
00:29:20,013 --> 00:29:22,223
I'm her daughter,

457
00:29:22,307 --> 00:29:23,933
so leave.

458
00:29:24,976 --> 00:29:27,437
Aren't you from Seoul?

459
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:29,189
She's my mom.

460
00:29:29,272 --> 00:29:30,607
No, she's mine!

461
00:29:34,444 --> 00:29:37,155
Mom, aren't you going to watch the soap opera?

462
00:29:37,238 --> 00:29:38,364
The soap opera?

463
00:29:41,701 --> 00:29:43,912
Well, I can't skip out on that.

464
00:29:44,829 --> 00:29:45,705
Let's go, my son.

465
00:29:49,751 --> 00:29:51,002
The soap opera.

466
00:29:54,672 --> 00:29:56,049
What was that?

467
00:29:57,008 --> 00:29:59,052
Jeez.

468
00:30:07,393 --> 00:30:08,728
MUST HAVE BEEN LOVE

469
00:30:08,812 --> 00:30:11,773
Hyun-woo and I have similar tastes.

470
00:30:23,743 --> 00:30:24,577
Are you sleeping?

471
00:30:44,806 --> 00:30:46,349
I'm about to.

472
00:30:46,432 --> 00:30:47,267
Why?

473
00:30:48,852 --> 00:30:51,396
I need to go to work early tomorrow,

474
00:30:51,479 --> 00:30:53,064
so I won't be able to see you…

475
00:30:57,944 --> 00:30:59,362
Going to work early tomorrow.

476
00:31:00,154 --> 00:31:02,198
When will you be coming home…

477
00:31:08,079 --> 00:31:09,163
Okay.

478
00:31:14,294 --> 00:31:16,212
Should I take tomorrow off?

479
00:31:16,296 --> 00:31:18,590
Can you just take tomorrow off?

480
00:31:36,941 --> 00:31:37,942
Good night.

481
00:31:44,198 --> 00:31:47,493
I'm going to listen to the songs on your MP3 before I sleep.

482
00:31:47,577 --> 00:31:50,121
Oh, that? How are the songs?

483
00:31:50,204 --> 00:31:51,748
They're all oldies.

484
00:31:51,831 --> 00:31:52,665
I like them.

485
00:31:53,333 --> 00:31:55,376
They're all my favorite songs.

486
00:31:55,460 --> 00:31:57,378
That MP3 isn't mine.

487
00:31:58,087 --> 00:31:59,923
-Then? -I picked it up in the past.

488
00:32:00,006 --> 00:32:03,134
I couldn't find the owner, so I kept it with me all along.

489
00:32:03,801 --> 00:32:04,886
Where did you find it?

490
00:32:04,969 --> 00:32:05,970
At my high school.

491
00:32:06,054 --> 00:32:07,639
On the field.

492
00:32:08,348 --> 00:32:11,225
Didn't you go to Hanil Foreign Language High School?

493
00:32:11,309 --> 00:32:13,895
Yes, I picked it up on my first day there.

494
00:32:32,080 --> 00:32:33,247
What?

495
00:32:34,874 --> 00:32:36,793
So this was mine?

496
00:32:40,004 --> 00:32:40,838
Wait.

497
00:33:04,862 --> 00:33:06,489
That was

498
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,616
Hyun-woo?

499
00:33:10,994 --> 00:33:12,787
Unbelievable.

500
00:33:14,497 --> 00:33:15,331
I mean…

501
00:33:16,791 --> 00:33:17,917
Was he born

502
00:33:18,584 --> 00:33:20,420
to love me or something?

503
00:33:21,921 --> 00:33:24,048
He fell for me in that brief moment,

504
00:33:24,132 --> 00:33:26,718
so he kept this all this time.

505
00:33:26,801 --> 00:33:30,013
He'll be so shocked if he finds out that the girl he fell for

506
00:33:30,638 --> 00:33:31,931
was me.

507
00:33:37,812 --> 00:33:40,481
But why do you still have it?

508
00:33:40,565 --> 00:33:43,109
She must've been so pretty.

509
00:33:44,152 --> 00:33:45,153
What…

510
00:33:50,658 --> 00:33:51,659
What is it?

511
00:33:55,038 --> 00:33:56,039
I don't…

512
00:33:58,583 --> 00:34:00,001
remember.

513
00:34:01,419 --> 00:34:02,754
You don't?

514
00:34:02,837 --> 00:34:03,838
Of course not.

515
00:34:03,921 --> 00:34:05,256
That was years ago.

516
00:34:06,549 --> 00:34:07,967
Exactly.

517
00:34:08,051 --> 00:34:11,888
The fact that you still kept this all these years must mean

518
00:34:11,971 --> 00:34:15,099
you couldn't get her out of your head.

519
00:34:15,850 --> 00:34:17,643
She must've been gorgeous.

520
00:34:20,063 --> 00:34:22,899
Come on. It's not like that.

521
00:34:22,982 --> 00:34:24,067
I can't even remember

522
00:34:24,150 --> 00:34:27,862
if the person was male, female, a teacher, a student,

523
00:34:27,945 --> 00:34:29,572
or a security guard.

524
00:34:29,655 --> 00:34:31,407
I can't remember a thing.

525
00:34:36,954 --> 00:34:38,372
Then why still keep it?

526
00:34:42,001 --> 00:34:43,252
I'm not keeping it.

527
00:34:44,504 --> 00:34:46,214
I just stashed it away.

528
00:34:49,842 --> 00:34:51,552
Okay. You can go.

529
00:34:53,554 --> 00:34:55,431
Go. Go sleep.

530
00:35:00,561 --> 00:35:01,646
What is it this time?

531
00:35:02,855 --> 00:35:04,398
The curtain.

532
00:35:05,483 --> 00:35:06,526
Make sure you draw it.

533
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:09,654
This room is facing east,

534
00:35:09,737 --> 00:35:11,697
so it gets pretty bright in the morning.

535
00:35:11,781 --> 00:35:13,407
Okay, so leave.

536
00:38:13,296 --> 00:38:15,089
Should I help?

537
00:38:15,631 --> 00:38:16,757
Will you?

538
00:38:16,841 --> 00:38:18,676
I'm going to make some japchae.

539
00:38:20,678 --> 00:38:22,930
Can you chop these carrots for me?

540
00:38:24,890 --> 00:38:25,725
Okay.

541
00:38:31,397 --> 00:38:34,567
Sweetie, be careful not to chop your fingers.

542
00:38:34,650 --> 00:38:37,611
You need to julienne it.

543
00:38:37,695 --> 00:38:42,033
Exactly how thin do you want me to chop them?

544
00:38:42,825 --> 00:38:45,411
Well… It's…

545
00:38:46,078 --> 00:38:47,246
Let me show you.

546
00:39:05,139 --> 00:39:06,807
-Mother. -Yes?

547
00:39:06,891 --> 00:39:08,642
You're incredible.

548
00:39:09,435 --> 00:39:11,312
What's so incredible about this?

549
00:39:15,524 --> 00:39:17,651
How could you say that? This is like

550
00:39:18,778 --> 00:39:20,154
modern art.

551
00:39:20,237 --> 00:39:21,364
Is that so?

552
00:39:22,239 --> 00:39:23,574
Goodness.

553
00:39:23,657 --> 00:39:25,368
That's a new one.

554
00:39:25,451 --> 00:39:27,328
You're making japchae, right?

555
00:39:27,411 --> 00:39:29,997
What else do you need to do?

556
00:39:30,915 --> 00:39:32,666
Next…

557
00:39:32,750 --> 00:39:34,835
I need to cook some eggs.

558
00:39:35,669 --> 00:39:37,755
-How exactly do you do that? -The eggs?

559
00:39:37,838 --> 00:39:39,673
It's a cakewalk. Should I show you?

560
00:39:41,008 --> 00:39:42,176
I'm excited.

561
00:39:49,809 --> 00:39:51,102
You're so incredible.

562
00:39:51,185 --> 00:39:52,311
I can use both hands.

563
00:39:54,980 --> 00:39:56,774
Goodness, Mother.

564
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,943
You're truly amazing.

565
00:39:59,026 --> 00:40:01,362
Am I? Should I give it a spin too?

566
00:40:01,445 --> 00:40:02,613
A spin?

567
00:40:04,073 --> 00:40:06,367
I was just joking.

568
00:40:07,827 --> 00:40:09,995
Why the change of heart?

569
00:40:10,079 --> 00:40:11,747
You said your villa was vacant.

570
00:40:11,831 --> 00:40:14,291
What's wrong? Is your husband against it?

571
00:40:14,917 --> 00:40:17,211
In case the reporters find out?

572
00:40:19,046 --> 00:40:20,756
He's unbelievable.

573
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:23,551
Who helped him whenever his business was failing?

574
00:40:23,634 --> 00:40:26,554
How could he do this to my husband of all people?

575
00:40:27,763 --> 00:40:28,764
Forget it.

576
00:40:29,765 --> 00:40:30,766
Unbelievable.

577
00:40:32,852 --> 00:40:34,395
Here you are.

578
00:40:35,729 --> 00:40:37,314
I was looking everywhere for you.

579
00:40:37,940 --> 00:40:39,024
Why me?

580
00:40:40,484 --> 00:40:42,319
They're clean now.

581
00:40:42,403 --> 00:40:43,654
They don't smell at all.

582
00:40:44,321 --> 00:40:45,406
Is that so?

583
00:40:45,489 --> 00:40:47,283
-Have them if you want. -Really?

584
00:40:47,950 --> 00:40:50,202
But they're extremely expensive.

585
00:40:50,286 --> 00:40:52,371
It's okay. They're yours.

586
00:40:55,082 --> 00:40:57,418
Then why don't you let me do your hair?

587
00:40:57,501 --> 00:40:58,586
I'm very skilled.

588
00:41:08,637 --> 00:41:10,556
What kind of hairstyle do you want?

589
00:41:10,639 --> 00:41:12,725
What can you do?

590
00:41:13,559 --> 00:41:14,977
Everything.

591
00:41:15,060 --> 00:41:19,064
I used to work in Cheongdam-dong, you know?

592
00:41:20,816 --> 00:41:23,527
Mi-seon, what is going on?

593
00:41:23,611 --> 00:41:26,655
This is the best twist ever since The Sixth Sense.

594
00:41:26,739 --> 00:41:28,741
Even my palms are sweaty.

595
00:41:28,824 --> 00:41:30,409
-Hey-- -You bad-mouthed that sly fox.

596
00:41:30,493 --> 00:41:32,870
Then I heard she suddenly appeared.

597
00:41:32,953 --> 00:41:34,705
That only happens in movies or dramas.

598
00:41:34,788 --> 00:41:36,790
This is more thrilling than any drama ending.

599
00:41:36,874 --> 00:41:38,584
-Yes. -So what happened?

600
00:41:38,667 --> 00:41:40,211
Guys, let's talk later.

601
00:41:41,003 --> 00:41:44,924
I heard Hae-in's mother is a psychopath.

602
00:41:45,799 --> 00:41:48,385
What do you mean? That's just nonsense.

603
00:41:48,469 --> 00:41:50,012
-Go! -Wait!

604
00:41:50,095 --> 00:41:54,183
I'm not leaving. My husband told me everything.

605
00:41:54,266 --> 00:41:56,936
I heard she stepped on dung the moment she arrived

606
00:41:57,019 --> 00:41:58,437
and cried a river.

607
00:42:02,816 --> 00:42:06,153
It's crazy. How could she step on dung as soon as she arrived?

608
00:42:07,154 --> 00:42:08,280
Let's be frank.

609
00:42:08,364 --> 00:42:11,408
-Your mom is the one who stepped in dung. -That's right.

610
00:42:11,492 --> 00:42:14,203
They're former in-laws who ended things on a bad note.

611
00:42:14,286 --> 00:42:16,956
That dirt-poor family fled in the middle of the night,

612
00:42:17,039 --> 00:42:18,457
and Ms. Jeon had to take them in.

613
00:42:18,541 --> 00:42:22,002
Yes, I saw the news. They have nothing to their names now.

614
00:42:22,086 --> 00:42:26,840
Your mom may look tough, but she's such a softie at heart.

615
00:42:26,924 --> 00:42:28,467
-Yes. -Thanks.

616
00:42:31,053 --> 00:42:34,765
By the way, isn't that woman so shameless?

617
00:42:34,848 --> 00:42:37,434
How dare she come here after what she's done?

618
00:42:37,518 --> 00:42:39,270
-Right. -You know what?

619
00:42:39,353 --> 00:42:41,855
I'd love to see her face just once.

620
00:42:41,939 --> 00:42:42,940
Me too.

621
00:42:43,023 --> 00:42:45,818
What? Is there something on my lips?

622
00:42:50,823 --> 00:42:51,991
Then look.

623
00:42:53,367 --> 00:42:55,703
You wanted to see me, so take a good look.

624
00:42:59,623 --> 00:43:01,542
Our assets are just frozen for now.

625
00:43:01,625 --> 00:43:02,918
We're not dirt-poor.

626
00:43:03,002 --> 00:43:06,255
Though it was late when we arrived, we didn't flee in the middle of the night.

627
00:43:06,338 --> 00:43:07,631
And we'll be leaving soon.

628
00:43:08,507 --> 00:43:10,968
We're not mooching off of them.

629
00:43:11,051 --> 00:43:12,219
Do you understand?

630
00:43:13,637 --> 00:43:14,680
-Yes. -Yes.

631
00:43:16,890 --> 00:43:18,142
Jeez.

632
00:43:18,225 --> 00:43:19,852
What do you take me for?

633
00:43:21,854 --> 00:43:22,855
Wait.

634
00:43:25,441 --> 00:43:26,442
Hey.

635
00:43:27,401 --> 00:43:29,028
You didn't have breakfast.

636
00:43:29,111 --> 00:43:32,156
I'm taking these to the orchard.

637
00:43:32,239 --> 00:43:34,575
The cold bean-soup noodles are tasty and refreshing.

638
00:43:34,658 --> 00:43:35,701
Would you like some?

639
00:43:43,083 --> 00:43:45,753
I don't have carbs during the day.

640
00:43:53,469 --> 00:43:56,764
Jeez. Then when will you have them?

641
00:44:06,315 --> 00:44:09,276
How do you feel about becoming the youngest chairman?

642
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:11,070
What's your plan?

643
00:44:11,153 --> 00:44:13,113
Is it any different from the previous management?

644
00:44:13,197 --> 00:44:16,158
There is rumor of a large-scale restructuring. Is it true?

645
00:44:16,241 --> 00:44:17,660
How is Chairman Hong doing?

646
00:44:24,667 --> 00:44:27,544
I plan to establish a corporation in Singapore by 2025

647
00:44:27,628 --> 00:44:31,256
so we can branch out to foreign markets.

648
00:44:31,340 --> 00:44:33,634
It'll cost us about 140 billion won to establish

649
00:44:33,717 --> 00:44:35,969
and run this corporation that'll serve as the foundation

650
00:44:36,053 --> 00:44:38,222
for department stores and supermarkets abroad.

651
00:44:38,305 --> 00:44:41,392
I visited Mr. Song at the penitentiary and spoke with him.

652
00:44:41,475 --> 00:44:45,187
I don't think he knows where the chairman's secret fund is.

653
00:44:45,270 --> 00:44:47,398
He created the fund and wired it abroad,

654
00:44:47,481 --> 00:44:49,983
but he doesn't know where it is.

655
00:44:50,693 --> 00:44:51,652
How's that possible?

656
00:44:51,735 --> 00:44:54,947
The chairman's office manually managed the ledger

657
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:56,990
and handed it to the chairman to be reviewed.

658
00:44:57,074 --> 00:45:01,662
The laundering process was complicated as they went through ten countries.

659
00:45:01,745 --> 00:45:05,666
The last destination was a bank in Labuan, Malaysia,

660
00:45:05,749 --> 00:45:07,209
but the money wasn't there.

661
00:45:16,844 --> 00:45:18,679
You wanted to see me, Chairman Yoon?

662
00:45:21,348 --> 00:45:22,307
You didn't hesitate

663
00:45:23,475 --> 00:45:25,018
to call me that.

664
00:45:25,102 --> 00:45:26,353
Why should I?

665
00:45:26,437 --> 00:45:27,563
Things have changed.

666
00:45:27,646 --> 00:45:30,858
I'm no longer a part of Queens or Hae-in's husband.

667
00:45:31,567 --> 00:45:32,401
I see.

668
00:45:33,694 --> 00:45:34,528
But it's a pity.

669
00:45:34,611 --> 00:45:38,657
I feel uncomfortable that you're still leading our Legal Team.

670
00:45:38,741 --> 00:45:40,743
Of course. I understand.

671
00:45:42,953 --> 00:45:43,787
Mr. Baek.

672
00:45:47,583 --> 00:45:48,542
Drop the act already.

673
00:45:54,465 --> 00:45:57,551
I'll be honest since you seem to know everything.

674
00:45:58,635 --> 00:45:59,720
I'm still waiting.

675
00:46:00,846 --> 00:46:03,807
I submitted my resume to Baekhwa, Taepung, Hwang &amp; Kim.

676
00:46:03,891 --> 00:46:06,852
We're still negotiating my salary, but it's not easy in this field.

677
00:46:06,935 --> 00:46:09,688
It's hard to raise your salary if you've been on a break.

678
00:46:09,772 --> 00:46:14,067
As you already know, I didn't receive any alimony.

679
00:46:14,151 --> 00:46:16,153
So I need to make this work.

680
00:46:16,779 --> 00:46:18,572
I only need one month.

681
00:46:19,448 --> 00:46:21,658
Could you please help me out?

682
00:46:23,702 --> 00:46:25,662
So you're looking for a new job?

683
00:46:25,746 --> 00:46:27,039
Correct. And as you know,

684
00:46:27,122 --> 00:46:30,459
I have no access to the Legal Team's classified documents.

685
00:46:30,542 --> 00:46:32,169
There's nothing to worry about.

686
00:46:37,132 --> 00:46:38,133
You may go.

687
00:46:41,762 --> 00:46:42,846
Where is she?

688
00:46:45,057 --> 00:46:46,225
Hae-in.

689
00:46:46,308 --> 00:46:48,143
Wasn't it you who picked her up yesterday?

690
00:46:53,649 --> 00:46:54,691
So where is she?

691
00:46:56,860 --> 00:46:57,694
I'm afraid

692
00:46:58,695 --> 00:47:00,113
I don't know either.

693
00:47:01,865 --> 00:47:04,535
You picked her up, but you don't know where she went?

694
00:47:05,494 --> 00:47:06,537
Exactly.

695
00:47:06,620 --> 00:47:08,205
I guess she couldn't trust me.

696
00:47:08,288 --> 00:47:11,041
She took the car and hasn't been picking up.

697
00:47:11,124 --> 00:47:12,709
Please let me know

698
00:47:12,793 --> 00:47:14,294
if you find her.

699
00:47:16,129 --> 00:47:16,964
Sure.

700
00:47:50,873 --> 00:47:53,792
You're the true owner of this teacup.

701
00:47:54,543 --> 00:47:56,169
It suits you much better.

702
00:47:56,253 --> 00:47:58,672
I love your outfit too.

703
00:47:58,755 --> 00:48:01,675
You look glamorous and elegant. That's rare.

704
00:48:01,758 --> 00:48:05,429
This is why I haven't been dressing up. It's easy for me to look glamorous.

705
00:48:06,763 --> 00:48:09,433
Please come by the spa before I close it down.

706
00:48:09,516 --> 00:48:11,560
Let me take care of you one last time.

707
00:48:11,643 --> 00:48:13,186
Are you closing it down?

708
00:48:15,606 --> 00:48:16,481
Sorry?

709
00:48:16,565 --> 00:48:18,191
Why? Hasn't business been good?

710
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:27,200
Of course, you should shut it down.

711
00:48:28,201 --> 00:48:29,036
Right?

712
00:48:29,119 --> 00:48:30,495
You've had it for a long time.

713
00:48:30,579 --> 00:48:31,747
Exactly.

714
00:48:31,830 --> 00:48:35,208
I thought I'd grow old while making others look more youthful.

715
00:48:36,251 --> 00:48:37,628
-That can't happen. -Right?

716
00:48:40,088 --> 00:48:43,008
Once I take office, I want to launch a cosmetic line

717
00:48:43,091 --> 00:48:44,968
with products from the department store.

718
00:48:45,052 --> 00:48:46,053
What do you say?

719
00:48:46,136 --> 00:48:49,222
Just like Lafayette or Harrods,

720
00:48:49,306 --> 00:48:51,725
we should give our store a luxurious reputation--

721
00:48:51,808 --> 00:48:52,851
Wait.

722
00:48:52,935 --> 00:48:53,977
"Take office"?

723
00:48:55,270 --> 00:48:56,980
-What? -Where?

724
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:00,525
Aren't I taking over Hae-in's spot?

725
00:49:01,735 --> 00:49:04,571
Would it look too weird if I took over right away?

726
00:49:04,655 --> 00:49:06,657
Then how about a director first?

727
00:49:14,414 --> 00:49:15,248
What is it?

728
00:49:17,584 --> 00:49:18,835
Close down your spa,

729
00:49:20,420 --> 00:49:22,714
pack up your stuff, and join Director Jo in the US.

730
00:49:22,798 --> 00:49:26,009
We have too much to lose if they catch you here.

731
00:49:27,594 --> 00:49:30,639
You can start a small cosmetic line there if you want.

732
00:49:31,223 --> 00:49:32,891
I'll look for some investors.

733
00:49:40,315 --> 00:49:43,068
You can shut down your business, move, and go into hiding.

734
00:49:43,151 --> 00:49:45,404
But one thing you can't change is your child's academy

735
00:49:45,487 --> 00:49:46,530
if you're a parent.

736
00:49:46,613 --> 00:49:47,948
His daughter is a senior.

737
00:49:48,031 --> 00:49:50,993
She's preparing to go to college by majoring in cello.

738
00:49:52,953 --> 00:49:56,665
I sued you for fraud and violating the Communications Privacy Act,

739
00:49:56,748 --> 00:49:59,042
but they couldn't send you the papers since you were gone.

740
00:49:59,126 --> 00:50:00,544
I looked everywhere for you.

741
00:50:13,390 --> 00:50:15,475
So he had this all along.

742
00:50:15,559 --> 00:50:16,810
He must've made a copy.

743
00:50:18,270 --> 00:50:19,312
Who is she?

744
00:50:23,859 --> 00:50:26,528
Soo-cheol, let me reveal the truth

745
00:50:26,611 --> 00:50:28,905
about your former wife, Cheon Da-hye.

746
00:50:29,573 --> 00:50:30,907
It might scare you a bit.

747
00:50:32,534 --> 00:50:35,537
You said you'd get rashes just eating next to an older woman.

748
00:50:36,121 --> 00:50:38,582
But you see, I'm five years your senior.

749
00:50:39,374 --> 00:50:43,003
Everything about my parents, their wealth, and my education is fake.

750
00:50:43,712 --> 00:50:47,090
One more. Geon-u isn't your son.

751
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:50,302
How was it not obvious?

752
00:50:50,385 --> 00:50:53,305
You have sharp features, while Geon-u's are soft.

753
00:50:53,388 --> 00:50:55,057
How could you not suspect it?

754
00:50:56,767 --> 00:50:58,935
I'm sad to leave you as well.

755
00:51:00,937 --> 00:51:03,148
I'll never meet another man like you.

756
00:51:03,231 --> 00:51:05,275
Are you going to marry me or not?

757
00:51:05,358 --> 00:51:06,318
I said no.

758
00:51:07,736 --> 00:51:10,280
Fine, but give me your gloves then.

759
00:51:11,907 --> 00:51:12,991
You're skittish yet clumsy.

760
00:51:13,075 --> 00:51:14,326
What's my name again?

761
00:51:14,409 --> 00:51:15,702
Cheon Da-hye.

762
00:51:15,786 --> 00:51:17,662
You're rich, but you're not too bright.

763
00:51:17,746 --> 00:51:21,208
Can you promise that I don't have to marry you?

764
00:51:21,291 --> 00:51:22,292
Yes.

765
00:51:22,375 --> 00:51:24,544
By the way, is that muffler warm?

766
00:51:42,062 --> 00:51:46,149
You should've recognized me after giving me everything I wanted.

767
00:51:47,150 --> 00:51:49,069
Please give them a round of applause

768
00:51:49,152 --> 00:51:51,738
as they begin their new journey.

769
00:51:56,076 --> 00:51:57,494
They're both good-looking.

770
00:51:58,286 --> 00:51:59,329
Hey.

771
00:51:59,412 --> 00:52:01,331
Don't make me frustrated.

772
00:52:01,414 --> 00:52:04,209
I was so annoyed when Hae-in refused to listen to me

773
00:52:04,292 --> 00:52:05,919
and chose that guy instead.

774
00:52:06,002 --> 00:52:08,922
You better seduce Soo-cheol and marry him right away.

775
00:52:09,589 --> 00:52:10,423
All right.

776
00:52:11,007 --> 00:52:12,551
Don't tell him your real name.

777
00:52:12,634 --> 00:52:13,844
Use a fake one.

778
00:52:13,927 --> 00:52:16,263
No, I'm going to use my real name.

779
00:52:16,346 --> 00:52:18,265
By the way, where is he?

780
00:52:19,015 --> 00:52:19,850
Over there.

781
00:52:20,392 --> 00:52:21,768
Don't ever get married.

782
00:52:21,852 --> 00:52:22,978
It's so hectic.

783
00:52:23,061 --> 00:52:24,020
-No way. -I know.

784
00:52:24,104 --> 00:52:26,398
That's the crybaby that I knew?

785
00:52:26,481 --> 00:52:28,358
He's so tall. Just my type.

786
00:52:28,441 --> 00:52:31,111
No, behind him.

787
00:52:41,705 --> 00:52:43,623
That fool. He hasn't changed.

788
00:52:43,707 --> 00:52:47,085
-Gosh. -Anyway, eat up since you're here anyway.

789
00:52:49,504 --> 00:52:50,338
Goodbye.

790
00:53:05,562 --> 00:53:06,938
-Sir. -It's nice to see you.

791
00:53:07,022 --> 00:53:09,024
Where have you been? I was looking for you.

792
00:53:09,107 --> 00:53:10,358
I'm glad you're here.

793
00:53:10,442 --> 00:53:11,651
Eat up.

794
00:53:11,735 --> 00:53:14,738
But you failed to recognize me.

795
00:53:29,169 --> 00:53:30,420
Hello.

796
00:53:30,503 --> 00:53:32,088
My name is Cheon Da-hye.

797
00:53:32,881 --> 00:53:33,715
"Cheon Da-hye"?

798
00:53:38,929 --> 00:53:41,014
That's a pretty name.

799
00:53:41,097 --> 00:53:42,807
And so is your face.

800
00:53:43,516 --> 00:53:44,893
I see.

801
00:53:46,645 --> 00:53:49,606
You haven't eaten yet.

802
00:53:49,689 --> 00:53:51,066
Let's see…

803
00:53:51,149 --> 00:53:52,901
Forget me

804
00:53:52,984 --> 00:53:55,779
like you have in the past.

805
00:53:55,862 --> 00:53:57,155
Geon-u too.

806
00:53:57,239 --> 00:54:00,033
It won't be hard. You're not that bright anyway.

807
00:54:10,835 --> 00:54:11,670
Hey.

808
00:54:14,130 --> 00:54:15,090
Why are you crying?

809
00:54:17,050 --> 00:54:19,886
Where will I find Da-hye?

810
00:54:25,642 --> 00:54:26,893
You can't.

811
00:54:26,977 --> 00:54:29,229
She took everything and probably went into hiding.

812
00:54:31,231 --> 00:54:34,276
No, you're wrong. She forgot something.

813
00:54:34,359 --> 00:54:35,443
What?

814
00:54:36,194 --> 00:54:37,612
Me.

815
00:54:39,698 --> 00:54:41,408
I'm still here.

816
00:54:42,951 --> 00:54:44,119
She used to say

817
00:54:45,412 --> 00:54:47,455
that I was the most precious person.

818
00:54:49,749 --> 00:54:52,335
So where did she go after leaving me behind?

819
00:55:29,247 --> 00:55:30,957
Gosh, are you up?

820
00:55:31,041 --> 00:55:32,250
Hi, you're up.

821
00:55:32,334 --> 00:55:34,336
Hold on.

822
00:55:47,182 --> 00:55:48,558
Look at this, Geon-u.

823
00:55:48,641 --> 00:55:51,519
It used to be my favorite doll.

824
00:55:57,650 --> 00:56:00,278
But what's the point of doing this now?

825
00:56:00,362 --> 00:56:01,988
The tables have been turned.

826
00:56:02,072 --> 00:56:03,907
-I'll turn them back again. -But how?

827
00:56:03,990 --> 00:56:07,118
Eun-sung didn't achieve what he did legally, and I'll prove that.

828
00:56:07,202 --> 00:56:08,286
Fine.

829
00:56:08,370 --> 00:56:11,706
Let's say it was illegal and we had all the proof.

830
00:56:11,790 --> 00:56:14,501
Filing a suit, attending trials, suing him again for the stocks…

831
00:56:14,584 --> 00:56:16,419
It'll take at least five years.

832
00:56:16,503 --> 00:56:17,962
-Are you sure? -I'll take a shortcut.

833
00:56:18,046 --> 00:56:19,547
-Which is? -Investment fraud.

834
00:56:20,965 --> 00:56:22,759
He schemed a two-trillion investment fraud

835
00:56:22,842 --> 00:56:24,636
from the get-go and lured the family

836
00:56:24,719 --> 00:56:27,180
with a new business idea to steal their stocks.

837
00:56:28,098 --> 00:56:31,309
They'll get their provisional seizures back if I can prove it.

838
00:56:31,393 --> 00:56:33,686
But most importantly, he'll lose his power.

839
00:56:33,770 --> 00:56:34,729
What about the stocks?

840
00:56:34,813 --> 00:56:36,689
The stocks would still be his.

841
00:56:37,232 --> 00:56:39,234
I'm going to use the same tactic he did.

842
00:56:47,200 --> 00:56:49,786
-What are you doing? -I just have a lot of time.

843
00:56:49,869 --> 00:56:52,622
They should give us new positions. I feel uneasy here.

844
00:56:52,705 --> 00:56:53,623
I felt bad.

845
00:56:54,249 --> 00:56:56,334
I've never rejected Mr. Hong's call before.

846
00:56:56,418 --> 00:56:57,377
Don't feel bad.

847
00:56:57,460 --> 00:57:00,130
It's best to cut ties immediately.

848
00:57:00,213 --> 00:57:02,674
Weren't you pretty close with Ms. Hong though?

849
00:57:02,757 --> 00:57:03,633
Who's that?

850
00:57:03,716 --> 00:57:05,260
-Gosh. -Gosh.

851
00:57:05,343 --> 00:57:09,597
Do you know why "friendship" and "loyalty" are abstract nouns?

852
00:57:09,681 --> 00:57:11,015
Because they don't exist.

853
00:57:14,227 --> 00:57:17,230
Secretary Na and Ms. Hong don't seem to be in touch at all.

854
00:57:17,313 --> 00:57:18,731
She's taking some time off.

855
00:57:18,815 --> 00:57:20,859
She's going to stay at a farm with her kid.

856
00:57:20,942 --> 00:57:23,069
-And Mr. Baek? -He has no work these days.

857
00:57:23,153 --> 00:57:25,363
So he's been writing resumes

858
00:57:25,447 --> 00:57:27,323
and attending job interviews too.

859
00:57:32,078 --> 00:57:34,831
I don't want to hear it! Bring out the executives!

860
00:57:34,914 --> 00:57:36,958
-Arrest them! -Arrest them!

861
00:57:37,041 --> 00:57:39,752
We demand that Queens resolve this investment fraud!

862
00:57:39,836 --> 00:57:41,629
Hey, what's your plan?

863
00:57:41,713 --> 00:57:42,630
They look livid.

864
00:57:42,714 --> 00:57:45,425
The legal director is also on their side!

865
00:57:45,508 --> 00:57:46,885
You married into that family!

866
00:57:46,968 --> 00:57:47,927
No, you're wrong.

867
00:57:48,011 --> 00:57:50,013
He's been fired from work and home.

868
00:57:50,096 --> 00:57:52,098
He has no influence whatsoever.

869
00:57:55,393 --> 00:57:56,728
Anyway…

870
00:57:57,562 --> 00:57:59,689
I came here to hear you out.

871
00:57:59,772 --> 00:58:01,441
We've already told our story.

872
00:58:01,524 --> 00:58:04,527
Queens lured us in by offering to pay five times the market price.

873
00:58:04,611 --> 00:58:06,738
Then they said the resort complex project fell through

874
00:58:06,821 --> 00:58:08,406
and offered only double?

875
00:58:10,241 --> 00:58:12,577
I think there was a double contract.

876
00:58:12,660 --> 00:58:14,871
-Let me see the contract and-- -Don't be absurd.

877
00:58:33,806 --> 00:58:35,391
ATTORNEY HWANG

878
00:58:41,397 --> 00:58:42,398
BANK PRESIDENT GU BON-JUN

879
00:58:51,241 --> 00:58:52,283
ASSEMBLYMAN HAN

880
00:58:52,367 --> 00:58:53,284
DIRECTOR RYU

881
00:58:54,661 --> 00:58:56,204
I'M IN A MEETING. I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

882
00:59:05,713 --> 00:59:06,714
Goodness!

883
00:59:07,215 --> 00:59:09,259
What are you doing out here?

884
00:59:11,052 --> 00:59:12,345
You work on the weekends too.

885
00:59:12,428 --> 00:59:13,429
Yes.

886
00:59:13,513 --> 00:59:16,099
The weeds never stop growing.

887
00:59:16,182 --> 00:59:18,393
There's nothing more we can ask for

888
00:59:18,476 --> 00:59:21,688
than some cold makgeolli and green onion pancakes

889
00:59:21,771 --> 00:59:24,983
after our morning work.

890
00:59:25,692 --> 00:59:26,526
I see.

891
00:59:26,609 --> 00:59:30,488
You're living a great life surrounded by nature.

892
00:59:30,572 --> 00:59:31,573
I'm envious.

893
00:59:33,533 --> 00:59:34,617
Goodness.

894
00:59:34,701 --> 00:59:37,704
People will laugh if they hear that a rich family

895
00:59:37,787 --> 00:59:39,956
is envious of some farmers.

896
00:59:40,832 --> 00:59:44,002
By the way, I'm not sure if you've had makgeolli before.

897
00:59:44,085 --> 00:59:45,211
I did once,

898
00:59:46,004 --> 00:59:48,423
out of curiosity, back in university 30 years ago.

899
00:59:51,092 --> 00:59:53,553
Then you should have some today.

900
00:59:58,641 --> 00:59:59,475
Goodness.

901
01:00:00,727 --> 01:00:02,103
-Here. -Goodness.

902
01:00:02,186 --> 01:00:04,230
Thank you.

903
01:00:05,648 --> 01:00:07,525
Okay.

904
01:00:07,609 --> 01:00:08,901
Then…

905
01:00:09,986 --> 01:00:13,906
We need to make a toast, but what should we say?

906
01:00:13,990 --> 01:00:17,160
How about "Health matters the most"?

907
01:00:19,537 --> 01:00:21,080
We can't say that

908
01:00:21,164 --> 01:00:24,959
since his father is bedridden.

909
01:00:25,043 --> 01:00:27,003
Then how about

910
01:00:27,086 --> 01:00:28,921
"It's wonderful to see you"?

911
01:00:29,005 --> 01:00:31,716
That won't work either

912
01:00:31,799 --> 01:00:33,509
since their current situation

913
01:00:34,636 --> 01:00:36,929
isn't that wonderful.

914
01:00:37,013 --> 01:00:38,139
Let's just

915
01:00:38,973 --> 01:00:39,891
clink our glasses.

916
01:00:39,974 --> 01:00:40,933
But…

917
01:01:01,913 --> 01:01:04,916
Goodness.

918
01:01:04,999 --> 01:01:06,209
Are you okay?

919
01:01:08,252 --> 01:01:09,295
Let's…

920
01:01:09,379 --> 01:01:10,380
Let's drink a bit more.

921
01:01:10,463 --> 01:01:13,049
Don't be silly. We should go home.

922
01:01:13,132 --> 01:01:15,426
No, I won't go back there.

923
01:01:16,636 --> 01:01:19,472
Gosh. Is our house uncomfortable?

924
01:01:19,555 --> 01:01:21,474
I do admit that it's shabbier than--

925
01:01:21,557 --> 01:01:24,435
No, that's not why!

926
01:01:26,562 --> 01:01:28,272
As the head of my family,

927
01:01:29,982 --> 01:01:33,236
I should comfort them and say

928
01:01:33,903 --> 01:01:36,197
that everything is fine.

929
01:01:36,280 --> 01:01:37,865
That things will pan out

930
01:01:38,658 --> 01:01:40,535
and that we should go back home tomorrow.

931
01:01:41,285 --> 01:01:44,539
But I can't say that right now.

932
01:01:45,248 --> 01:01:47,208
I'm too ashamed to face them.

933
01:01:47,291 --> 01:01:49,585
I don't want to go home either.

934
01:01:49,669 --> 01:01:51,796
Oh, dear.

935
01:01:53,297 --> 01:01:54,340
Earlier today,

936
01:01:54,424 --> 01:01:58,052
I called my closest friend.

937
01:01:59,137 --> 01:02:01,514
I had never asked for such a favor before,

938
01:02:01,597 --> 01:02:06,102
but I asked him for just 20 million since we had no money.

939
01:02:06,185 --> 01:02:07,437
And?

940
01:02:08,604 --> 01:02:09,689
He said no.

941
01:02:09,772 --> 01:02:11,899
He was hesitant to give me money

942
01:02:11,983 --> 01:02:15,236
since we'd be interrogated by the prosecution soon,

943
01:02:15,319 --> 01:02:17,113
and reporters are looking for us.

944
01:02:17,196 --> 01:02:18,406
I see.

945
01:02:18,489 --> 01:02:20,116
I was dumbfounded.

946
01:02:20,199 --> 01:02:23,119
I can understand why you were dumbfounded

947
01:02:23,202 --> 01:02:25,163
since he was your closest friend.

948
01:02:25,246 --> 01:02:27,039
No, not because of him.

949
01:02:28,166 --> 01:02:30,835
By the fact that I didn't even have 20 million won.

950
01:02:31,502 --> 01:02:35,965
I had recently signed a tax invoice worth 45.6 billion won.

951
01:02:36,048 --> 01:02:39,594
But now, I don't even have 20 million in my pocket.

952
01:02:39,677 --> 01:02:42,430
I feel utterly pathetic.

953
01:02:47,101 --> 01:02:48,102
Look.

954
01:02:49,937 --> 01:02:52,815
I don't know if this will comfort you.

955
01:02:53,524 --> 01:02:54,400
Okay.

956
01:02:54,484 --> 01:02:55,735
But no one does.

957
01:02:57,195 --> 01:02:59,155
No one has that much in their pockets.

958
01:02:59,906 --> 01:03:03,409
Mr. Baek! I know you're lying just to make me feel better!

959
01:03:03,493 --> 01:03:05,536
I mean it!

960
01:03:05,620 --> 01:03:07,371
I've never had that much before!

961
01:03:13,628 --> 01:03:14,587
All right.

962
01:03:14,670 --> 01:03:15,838
We'll talk again later.

963
01:03:17,465 --> 01:03:18,299
Aunt Hae-in.

964
01:03:22,678 --> 01:03:23,721
Hey.

965
01:03:23,805 --> 01:03:27,266
I heard that you're in a pickle right now.

966
01:03:27,350 --> 01:03:28,267
A bit.

967
01:03:28,976 --> 01:03:29,894
It's a long story.

968
01:03:29,977 --> 01:03:32,230
I heard it's a secret that you're here.

969
01:03:32,313 --> 01:03:35,483
Don't worry. No one will hear a peep from our end.

970
01:03:35,566 --> 01:03:36,526
"Our end"?

971
01:03:36,609 --> 01:03:37,860
The Yongdu-ri Internet cafe.

972
01:03:37,944 --> 01:03:40,404
I pretty much run the place.

973
01:03:40,488 --> 01:03:41,447
I see.

974
01:03:41,948 --> 01:03:42,865
Okay.

975
01:03:46,828 --> 01:03:48,037
Thanks.

976
01:04:19,902 --> 01:04:21,279
Goodness, she's up.

977
01:04:21,362 --> 01:04:22,989
-Hae-in. -Are you okay, Hae-in?

978
01:04:25,241 --> 01:04:27,618
Have some water, sweetie.

979
01:04:32,248 --> 01:04:34,125
Shouldn't you go to the hospital?

980
01:04:34,208 --> 01:04:35,126
Shouldn't you?

981
01:04:36,252 --> 01:04:37,461
I'm okay.

982
01:04:38,296 --> 01:04:40,339
I couldn't sleep well last night, so I felt dizzy.

983
01:04:40,423 --> 01:04:41,799
Are you taking your medication?

984
01:04:42,508 --> 01:04:44,635
What medication? Is she sick?

985
01:04:46,178 --> 01:04:47,305
It's for my anemia.

986
01:04:47,388 --> 01:04:48,264
You have anemia?

987
01:04:48,347 --> 01:04:50,474
Your checkup results never showed that.

988
01:04:50,558 --> 01:04:51,475
How bad is it?

989
01:04:51,559 --> 01:04:53,603
Jeez, don't be so dramatic.

990
01:04:53,686 --> 01:04:55,563
I'm anemic too.

991
01:04:55,646 --> 01:04:58,316
I'm also dizzy since I couldn't sleep much either.

992
01:04:58,399 --> 01:05:00,651
It's not like Soo-cheol is doing fine either.

993
01:05:01,319 --> 01:05:03,029
We're all suffering here.

994
01:05:04,780 --> 01:05:08,993
Even still, it's not normal to faint.

995
01:05:09,535 --> 01:05:13,289
Tag along with Hyun-woo to Seoul tomorrow and visit a hospital.

996
01:05:13,372 --> 01:05:14,206
Okay, I'll do that.

997
01:05:18,836 --> 01:05:21,297
What? I'm tired.

998
01:05:21,380 --> 01:05:23,716
Why are you so harsh to Hae-in?

999
01:05:23,799 --> 01:05:26,552
-When was I? -She's sick.

1000
01:05:26,636 --> 01:05:28,054
She fainted.

1001
01:05:28,596 --> 01:05:30,389
Even a stranger would be concerned.

1002
01:05:31,223 --> 01:05:33,059
It's okay. Her mother-in-law--

1003
01:05:33,142 --> 01:05:35,645
No, her former mother-in-law takes good care of her anyway.

1004
01:05:35,728 --> 01:05:36,938
Didn't you see?

1005
01:05:37,021 --> 01:05:39,398
Hae-in didn't hesitate to obey her.

1006
01:05:39,482 --> 01:05:42,693
Has she ever done the same to me?

1007
01:05:43,527 --> 01:05:46,489
Seon-hwa, do you think you know everything about Hae-in?

1008
01:05:47,239 --> 01:05:50,993
No, of course not. And there's no need for that.

1009
01:05:54,538 --> 01:05:55,790
Seon-hwa.

1010
01:05:55,873 --> 01:05:56,958
What?

1011
01:05:58,626 --> 01:06:00,169
Gosh.

1012
01:06:01,087 --> 01:06:01,963
Seon-hwa!

1013
01:06:02,046 --> 01:06:03,839
What's wrong with you?

1014
01:06:03,923 --> 01:06:05,466
Stop calling my name.

1015
01:06:05,549 --> 01:06:06,550
Hae-in is…

1016
01:06:06,634 --> 01:06:07,760
What about her?

1017
01:06:13,015 --> 01:06:14,976
Just do me this favor.

1018
01:06:15,059 --> 01:06:17,478
Treat her well so you won't regret it later on.

1019
01:06:17,561 --> 01:06:19,021
Please.

1020
01:06:20,189 --> 01:06:21,649
Why would I regret it?

1021
01:06:21,732 --> 01:06:23,985
I never do things that I regret.

1022
01:06:28,364 --> 01:06:30,866
God, this is so upsetting.

1023
01:06:31,742 --> 01:06:34,412
She's going to be so heartbroken.

1024
01:06:36,038 --> 01:06:36,872
Gosh.

1025
01:07:01,856 --> 01:07:04,608
Why aren't any of my exes like him?

1026
01:07:17,121 --> 01:07:18,622
I called your doctor.

1027
01:07:18,706 --> 01:07:20,708
-You can see him tomorrow. -Sit down.

1028
01:07:26,714 --> 01:07:28,424
What have you been up to?

1029
01:07:29,091 --> 01:07:29,925
What?

1030
01:07:30,968 --> 01:07:34,055
Some days, he was covered in eggs.

1031
01:07:57,453 --> 01:07:58,454
LAND PURCHASE AGREEMENT

1032
01:07:58,537 --> 01:07:59,747
Secretary Na?

1033
01:08:00,790 --> 01:08:03,000
Let's have a meeting in the office pantry.

1034
01:08:03,084 --> 01:08:04,085
Okay.

1035
01:08:07,004 --> 01:08:09,548
I think he's been meeting

1036
01:08:09,632 --> 01:08:11,175
with those land protestors.

1037
01:08:11,258 --> 01:08:12,426
All right.

1038
01:08:12,510 --> 01:08:13,511
We'll talk again later.

1039
01:08:13,594 --> 01:08:15,554
Were you in touch with her?

1040
01:08:18,933 --> 01:08:21,227
Tell me how much you found out

1041
01:08:21,936 --> 01:08:22,770
behind my back.

1042
01:08:25,689 --> 01:08:27,817
It's your typical real estate investment fraud.

1043
01:08:27,900 --> 01:08:30,444
A broker bought the land in question from the owners

1044
01:08:30,528 --> 01:08:32,655
and offered five times the market price.

1045
01:08:32,738 --> 01:08:35,533
Then they signed a contract with Queens for one-third of that price.

1046
01:08:35,616 --> 01:08:36,909
A double contract?

1047
01:08:37,660 --> 01:08:39,120
That's deliberate fraud.

1048
01:08:39,203 --> 01:08:40,329
We need to prove that.

1049
01:08:40,412 --> 01:08:42,164
And the broker? You mentioned one.

1050
01:08:42,248 --> 01:08:43,707
Is he in Korea? Did he flee already?

1051
01:08:43,791 --> 01:08:45,543
PARADISE LAND, LTD

1052
01:08:58,889 --> 01:09:00,349
He did disappear,

1053
01:09:01,934 --> 01:09:03,978
but he's getting married this weekend.

1054
01:09:05,062 --> 01:09:07,481
I think he plans to fly out immediately afterward.

1055
01:09:08,190 --> 01:09:09,733
But he won't be able to.

1056
01:09:09,817 --> 01:09:11,443
I persuaded the landowners to sue

1057
01:09:11,527 --> 01:09:13,237
and put him on the No Fly List today.

1058
01:09:15,781 --> 01:09:18,325
Things will pan out once we catch him.

1059
01:09:19,034 --> 01:09:19,869
Yes.

1060
01:09:20,494 --> 01:09:22,705
But you shouldn't concern yourself

1061
01:09:22,788 --> 01:09:24,248
with this matter.

1062
01:09:24,331 --> 01:09:25,624
Why not? Why shouldn't I?

1063
01:09:28,878 --> 01:09:29,712
Look at me.

1064
01:09:29,795 --> 01:09:30,880
I'm dying.

1065
01:09:31,589 --> 01:09:34,258
Our family's ruined. We're dirt-poor and homeless.

1066
01:09:34,341 --> 01:09:35,885
My grandfather is in a coma.

1067
01:09:35,968 --> 01:09:36,927
Da-hye ran off.

1068
01:09:37,011 --> 01:09:38,345
Soo-cheol is out of it.

1069
01:09:38,429 --> 01:09:39,388
But the worst part

1070
01:09:40,181 --> 01:09:42,183
is that I'm in my ex-husband's hometown.

1071
01:09:44,810 --> 01:09:45,644
Is that

1072
01:09:46,478 --> 01:09:47,479
so terrible?

1073
01:09:47,563 --> 01:09:50,232
I need to do something

1074
01:09:50,316 --> 01:09:51,483
in this situation.

1075
01:09:51,567 --> 01:09:54,111
Today, I even gave myself the injection that'd raise my WBC.

1076
01:09:54,195 --> 01:09:55,654
I don't want to sit still.

1077
01:09:55,738 --> 01:09:58,073
I see. You did well.

1078
01:09:59,116 --> 01:10:01,744
Yes, I'll be able to get back on my feet

1079
01:10:01,827 --> 01:10:03,913
if I keep this up.

1080
01:10:04,997 --> 01:10:07,333
And you'll be able to leave me without feeling worried.

1081
01:10:08,626 --> 01:10:10,669
Then we'll finally part ways

1082
01:10:12,087 --> 01:10:13,505
like a true divorced couple.

1083
01:10:14,215 --> 01:10:15,216
That's my goal.

1084
01:10:16,091 --> 01:10:17,885
To part ways with you for good.

1085
01:10:26,518 --> 01:10:27,519
I'll share everything

1086
01:10:28,604 --> 01:10:30,189
with you from now on.

1087
01:10:30,272 --> 01:10:32,066
Let's do everything we can

1088
01:10:32,733 --> 01:10:34,610
as long as your body can take it.

1089
01:10:35,778 --> 01:10:36,987
You should reach your goal

1090
01:10:37,905 --> 01:10:39,073
as soon as possible.

1091
01:10:40,908 --> 01:10:41,742
Right.

1092
01:11:57,609 --> 01:11:58,610
ID CARD HONG HAE-IN

1093
01:12:05,326 --> 01:12:07,369
SUNGMIN UNIVERSITY MEDICAL CENTER HONG HAE-IN

1094
01:12:13,292 --> 01:12:15,836
SUNGMIN UNIVERSITY MEDICAL CENTER

1095
01:12:15,919 --> 01:12:17,129
I'll park and come up.

1096
01:12:17,880 --> 01:12:18,756
Okay.

1097
01:12:20,007 --> 01:12:21,633
ARE YOU THE PATIENT? YES

1098
01:12:23,927 --> 01:12:25,346
REISSUE PREVIOUS DOCUMENTS

1099
01:12:25,429 --> 01:12:27,014
LOADING

1100
01:12:34,188 --> 01:12:35,814
REFERRAL

1101
01:12:43,822 --> 01:12:45,991
TUMOR CELLS HAVE SPREAD BETWEEN CRANIAL NERVES

1102
01:12:46,075 --> 01:12:47,951
TREATMENT UNSUCCESSFUL DUE TO LOW WBC

1103
01:12:54,083 --> 01:12:56,710
AVERAGE ESTIMATED LIFE EXPECTANCY TO BE THREE MONTHS

1104
01:13:29,284 --> 01:13:31,578
Wait! What's your name?

1105
01:13:33,831 --> 01:13:36,166
Even the hospital director refused to tell me your name,

1106
01:13:36,250 --> 01:13:37,709
but I finally get to meet you.

1107
01:13:37,793 --> 01:13:39,211
You wrote this diagnosis.

1108
01:13:40,587 --> 01:13:41,672
So tell me.

1109
01:13:42,548 --> 01:13:44,258
How can I save Hong Hae-in?

1110
01:13:44,842 --> 01:13:46,427
That's all I need to know.

1111
01:14:04,987 --> 01:14:06,989
Why are you here? I'm going to the doctor's office.

1112
01:14:07,072 --> 01:14:08,490
The doctor called.

1113
01:14:08,574 --> 01:14:10,033
Eun-sung came by.

1114
01:14:24,423 --> 01:14:25,507
I'm sorry.

1115
01:14:25,591 --> 01:14:29,470
You're neither her family nor guardian, so I'm not obligated to tell you.

1116
01:14:29,553 --> 01:14:31,513
I have nothing to say.

1117
01:14:31,597 --> 01:14:32,431
Is that so?

1118
01:14:33,599 --> 01:14:35,851
Will you tell me if I become her guardian?

1119
01:14:38,187 --> 01:14:39,938
YONGDU-RI SUPERMARKET

1120
01:14:42,191 --> 01:14:43,025
Hello.

1121
01:14:43,609 --> 01:14:45,235
Aren't you hungry?

1122
01:14:45,319 --> 01:14:46,695
Please sit here.

1123
01:14:50,616 --> 01:14:51,492
So…

1124
01:14:52,409 --> 01:14:53,410
You see…

1125
01:14:53,494 --> 01:14:54,328
Yes?

1126
01:14:54,411 --> 01:14:58,165
An old lady lent me her handkerchief.

1127
01:14:58,248 --> 01:14:59,708
What old lady?

1128
01:15:00,501 --> 01:15:03,378
So… She…

1129
01:15:04,129 --> 01:15:07,174
She had a son.

1130
01:15:07,257 --> 01:15:08,926
I see. And his name was?

1131
01:15:09,009 --> 01:15:10,344
I'm not sure.

1132
01:15:11,011 --> 01:15:12,596
He looked ordinary.

1133
01:15:13,180 --> 01:15:15,307
He looked like Leslie Cheung.

1134
01:15:15,933 --> 01:15:17,935
In our neighborhood?

1135
01:15:18,018 --> 01:15:19,019
No, I doubt it.

1136
01:15:19,102 --> 01:15:21,605
He had a great voice too.

1137
01:15:21,688 --> 01:15:23,982
Like that of a singer.

1138
01:15:24,066 --> 01:15:27,945
A man who looks like Leslie Cheung and has the voice of a singer.

1139
01:15:28,028 --> 01:15:29,404
In our neighborhood?

1140
01:15:30,280 --> 01:15:34,243
Unless it was a ghost, I'm afraid you're mistaken.

1141
01:15:35,577 --> 01:15:36,578
No, I'm not.

1142
01:15:37,454 --> 01:15:38,664
They look similar.

1143
01:15:45,754 --> 01:15:46,797
Goodness.

1144
01:15:46,880 --> 01:15:47,881
They're here.

1145
01:15:52,386 --> 01:15:53,595
Are you hungry?

1146
01:15:53,679 --> 01:15:55,514
-Yes. -Okay, let's eat.

1147
01:15:57,182 --> 01:15:59,351
Great timing.

1148
01:15:59,434 --> 01:16:00,978
Dinner is ready. Let's eat.

1149
01:16:01,061 --> 01:16:01,979
What's for dinner?

1150
01:16:02,062 --> 01:16:03,355
I made braised short ribs.

1151
01:16:03,438 --> 01:16:04,898
-Braised short ribs? -It's sweet.

1152
01:16:04,982 --> 01:16:06,942
-I hope that's okay. -Did you add chestnuts too?

1153
01:16:07,025 --> 01:16:07,859
Did you…

1154
01:16:32,884 --> 01:16:34,595
Did Grace visit you?

1155
01:16:35,596 --> 01:16:36,638
Did you tell her no?

1156
01:16:37,973 --> 01:16:39,224
Yes, I did.

1157
01:16:39,308 --> 01:16:42,144
Well done. She needs to know her place.

1158
01:16:42,811 --> 01:16:45,897
Send out a press release and say that I'll take over the department store.

1159
01:16:45,981 --> 01:16:47,691
No, that's Hae-in's spot.

1160
01:16:52,154 --> 01:16:52,988
What are you saying?

1161
01:16:53,071 --> 01:16:54,740
She's coming back.

1162
01:16:54,823 --> 01:16:56,575
I'll manage it until then.

1163
01:17:00,162 --> 01:17:02,623
He won't die that easily.

1164
01:17:02,706 --> 01:17:04,458
I'm going to take great care of him

1165
01:17:04,541 --> 01:17:07,377
so that he lives but remains unconscious.

1166
01:17:11,298 --> 01:17:16,136
As long as he's in a coma, I am in charge of 21% of the stocks.

1167
01:17:16,803 --> 01:17:18,055
Do you understand?

1168
01:17:28,315 --> 01:17:30,484
TAKE ME OFF THE NO FLY LIST THIS IS YOUR ONLY WARNING

1169
01:18:06,019 --> 01:18:07,354
MR. YOON EUN-SUNG

1170
01:18:09,898 --> 01:18:11,650
What have you done?

1171
01:18:11,733 --> 01:18:12,776
I told you.

1172
01:18:12,859 --> 01:18:14,403
We don't share the same goal.

1173
01:18:14,486 --> 01:18:15,570
Where is the chairman?

1174
01:18:15,654 --> 01:18:17,239
You shouldn't do this.

1175
01:18:17,322 --> 01:18:19,157
What if he dies?

1176
01:18:19,241 --> 01:18:20,534
Then it can't be helped.

1177
01:18:59,865 --> 01:19:00,782
HONG HAE-IN

1178
01:19:00,866 --> 01:19:01,700
I'm leaving now.

1179
01:19:55,879 --> 01:19:58,507
Where are you going this late? Let's have dinner.

1180
01:19:58,590 --> 01:19:59,508
I'm just going

1181
01:20:00,217 --> 01:20:01,218
for a walk.

1182
01:20:02,844 --> 01:20:05,722
I think Hyun-woo is coming soon.

1183
01:20:05,806 --> 01:20:06,681
Is he?

1184
01:20:07,265 --> 01:20:08,350
Yes.

1185
01:20:08,433 --> 01:20:10,977
We should wait and eat with him.

1186
01:20:11,061 --> 01:20:12,312
All right then.

1187
01:20:16,775 --> 01:20:18,652
Don't go too far, okay?

1188
01:20:19,361 --> 01:20:20,195
Okay.

1189
01:21:12,497 --> 01:21:14,249
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1190
01:21:47,073 --> 01:21:48,116
Hyun-woo?

1191
01:21:48,867 --> 01:21:50,285
BAEK HYUN-WOO

1192
01:22:33,662 --> 01:22:34,871
Mr. Pyeon Seong-uk?

1193
01:22:36,414 --> 01:22:38,041
I've been looking for you.

1194
01:22:38,124 --> 01:22:39,960
I see. I should be

1195
01:22:40,043 --> 01:22:42,379
in Boracay right now after my wedding.

1196
01:22:42,462 --> 01:22:44,923
But things have become complicated, thanks to you.

1197
01:22:45,423 --> 01:22:46,716
Did you get my text?

1198
01:22:46,800 --> 01:22:47,717
I replied and said

1199
01:22:48,802 --> 01:22:50,428
we should deal with it legally

1200
01:22:54,099 --> 01:22:55,725
since I won't drop the suit.

1201
01:23:58,121 --> 01:23:59,831
Exactly.

1202
01:23:59,914 --> 01:24:03,501
The fact that you still kept this all these years must mean

1203
01:24:03,585 --> 01:24:06,296
you couldn't get her out of your head.

1204
01:24:07,088 --> 01:24:08,757
She must've been gorgeous.

1205
01:24:10,967 --> 01:24:11,968
Come on.

1206
01:24:12,594 --> 01:24:14,763
It's not like that.

1207
01:24:14,846 --> 01:24:15,972
I can't even remember

1208
01:24:16,056 --> 01:24:17,766
if the person was male, female,

1209
01:24:17,849 --> 01:24:20,101
a teacher, a student,

1210
01:24:20,185 --> 01:24:23,772
or a security guard. I can't remember a thing.

1211
01:24:24,773 --> 01:24:25,815
That was close.

1212
01:24:26,441 --> 01:24:29,235
She sure is sharp just like a CEO should be.

1213
01:24:29,319 --> 01:24:30,653
How could she get it right away?

1214
01:24:30,737 --> 01:24:34,365
As soon as she saw it, her gut told her that it belonged to a woman.

1215
01:24:34,449 --> 01:24:35,867
It was close.

1216
01:24:35,950 --> 01:24:37,077
I almost got caught.

1217
01:24:37,160 --> 01:24:39,454
Didn't you say

1218
01:24:39,537 --> 01:24:41,039
you searched the entire school

1219
01:24:41,122 --> 01:24:43,958
for that girl just like the prince from Cinderella?

1220
01:24:47,504 --> 01:24:48,338
I did.

1221
01:24:49,547 --> 01:24:50,757
She was really pretty.

1222
01:24:58,890 --> 01:25:00,767
-Do you still remember that? -Vividly.

1223
01:25:00,850 --> 01:25:02,268
She was my ideal type.

1224
01:25:02,352 --> 01:25:04,020
Do you think you'd recognize her?

1225
01:25:04,687 --> 01:25:05,563
Right away.

1226
01:25:05,647 --> 01:25:07,148
I know it's too late,

1227
01:25:07,232 --> 01:25:10,610
but maybe she was your destiny.

1228
01:25:14,614 --> 01:25:16,825
I wonder where she is and what she's doing.

1229
01:25:24,040 --> 01:25:26,960
QUEEN OF TEARS

1230
01:25:57,198 --> 01:25:59,742
-What humiliation did he get? -I'm going to kill you!

1231
01:25:59,826 --> 01:26:02,787
Even still, I would've made the same choice.

1232
01:26:02,871 --> 01:26:06,082
You should know by now that I do anything I set my mind to.

1233
01:26:06,374 --> 01:26:08,334
No amount of money can buy this experience.

1234
01:26:08,418 --> 01:26:10,211
-You told me to hold it! -Nepotism?

1235
01:26:10,295 --> 01:26:12,797
Will he move out? Does he want to live with you?

1236
01:26:12,881 --> 01:26:14,424
No way. Is he jealous?

1237
01:26:15,675 --> 01:26:18,386
From what I heard, he's feigning ignorance.

1238
01:26:18,469 --> 01:26:21,556
I have a knack for revealing truths.

1239
01:26:22,348 --> 01:26:24,058
There's something I must do.

1240
01:26:24,142 --> 01:26:25,935
You're really testing my patience,

1241
01:26:26,019 --> 01:26:27,520
so just get lost.

1242
01:26:34,444 --> 01:26:36,446
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim
